    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 5000i and 9000i - HEATER AND AIR CONDITIONER - TROUBLESHOOTING -
        Recirculation Motor-Cab
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Recirculation Motor-Cab</title>
        <table id="t0822405" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Recirculation Motor-Cab</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.55in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.70in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.86in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.68in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.58in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect recirculation motor connector (1059). Move key switch to ignition position.
                                Measure voltage from circuit 75BG to ground while changing from MAX to OFF with the mode
                                selector.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(1059), circuit 75BG to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>The voltage should change as the control is changed.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of incorrect voltage in circuit 75BG, from HVAC control (1057), then
                                repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At recirculation motor connector (1059), measure voltage from circuit 75BM to
                                ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Voltage from circuit 75BM to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of incorrect voltage in circuit 75BM, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Measure resistance between recirculation motor connector (1059) circuit 75-GK to
                                ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(1059) circuit 75-GK to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open in circuit 75-GK, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Re-install connector (1059). Turn ignition on. check if the recirculation motor
                                operates while the mode selector is changed.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Recir- cula- tion motor operates.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Cab recir- cula- tion controls check good.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace air distribution recirculation motor.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
    </svcproc>
